Problem G5: Hospital Queue Manager

Difficulty: Intermediate

Scenario

A large hospital manages different queues throughout the day. Patients wait to meet doctors, appointments are scheduled in sequence, and doctors may also be assigned to departments using queue-based scheduling.

Instead of creating separate queue implementations for each entity, the hospital wants a single reusable queue management system.

Requirements

Create a generic queue manager capable of handling any type of hospital-related object.

Create the Following Classes

Doctor
Fields:
doctorId
doctorName
specialization

Patient
Fields:
patientId
patientName
age

Appointment
Fields:
appointmentId
appointmentDate
purpose

Create Generic Queue Manager
QueueManager<T>
Implement Operations
void enqueue(T item)
T dequeue()
void displayQueue()

Expected Behavior
The queue should follow FIFO (First-In-First-Out) principles.

Sample Output
Patient Queue
1. Ram Sharma
2. Sita Karki
3. Hari Joshi

Dequeued: Ram Sharma

Remaining Queue
1. Sita Karki
2. Hari Joshi

Constraints
QueueManager must work for all entity types.
Avoid duplicate queue implementations.
Use Generics for type safety.

Concepts Practiced
Generic Classes
Queue Data Structures
Type Safety